# =============================================================================
# Cloudflare Zones File
# =============================================================================
# List your domains or zone IDs here, one per line.
# This file is used with the -zf|--zones-file argument.
#
# Supported formats:
#   - Domain names: example.com
#   - Zone IDs: abc123def456789012345678901234567 (32 character hex)
#
# Comments:
#   - Lines starting with # are ignored
#   - Inline comments are supported: example.com # production site
#
# =============================================================================

# Production Sites
site1.com                    # Main production site
site2.com                    # Secondary site
www.site3.com                # With subdomain

# Staging/Development
staging.site1.com            # Staging environment
dev.site1.com                # Development

# Client Sites
client1-site.com
client2-site.com

# Using Zone IDs (useful for zones without DNS access)
# abc123def456789012345678901234567

# =============================================================================
# Usage Examples:
# =============================================================================
# Apply rules to all zones in this file:
#   ./cloudflare-wordpress-rules.sh -zf zones.txt -c create-rules default
#
# Combine with additional domains:
#   ./cloudflare-wordpress-rules.sh -zf zones.txt -d extra.com -c list-rules
#
# Skip confirmation prompt:
#   ./cloudflare-wordpress-rules.sh -zf zones.txt -c delete-rules -y
# =============================================================================
